# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MedinovAI org-wide .gitignore baseline (v1, 2026-04-18)
#
# Maintainer: medinovai-infrastructure
# Purpose:    prevent the five most common secret-leak patterns observed in
#             medinovai-health over 2025-2026. Copy this file into the root
#             of every repository as `.gitignore` and APPEND any repo-specific
#             ignores BELOW the "=== repo-specific overrides ===" marker.
#
# Rationale for each block is inline. Do not remove blocks without opening an
# issue on medinovai-infrastructure explaining why.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Environment files ------------------------------------------------------
# The ATS, Cognaium, and medinovaios leaks (incident CyberSecurity#14, April
# 2026) all originated from committed .env / .env.production files. Never
# track any .env variant — ship a sanitized *.env*.example instead.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.*.example

# --- Session / agent backups -----------------------------------------------
# The zeroTouchMarketing / atlas-os / core-platform mirrors of the OpenAI
# key (`sk-proj-yxGaT6a...`, incident CyberSecurity#14) were inside
# agent session logs. Never track them.
**/agent-transcripts/
**/session-logs/
**/.cursor/projects/
**/state.backup-*/
**/*.jsonl.reset.*

# --- Secrets, keys, tokens --------------------------------------------------
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.keystore
.vault-init.json
.credentials.env
vault-token
root-token
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*-credentials.json
*-service-account.json
gcp-sa-*.json

# --- Kubernetes realised secrets -------------------------------------------
# Sealed / template manifests are fine; decoded / realised secret values are
# not. Use the suffix convention below.
*secret-values.yaml
*secrets-decoded.yaml
*sealed-secret-unsealed.yaml

# --- Python -----------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
env/
venv/
.venv/
.ci-*-venv/
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
.eggs/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/

# --- Node / Next.js ---------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
.next/
.nuxt/
.out/
.turbo/
.parcel-cache/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Terraform / Pulumi -----------------------------------------------------
# tfstate files routinely carry live credentials and resource IDs.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl
*.tfvars
!*.tfvars.example
crash.log

# --- IDE / OS ---------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# --- MedinovAI tooling ------------------------------------------------------
.jcodemunch/
.cursor/worktrees/
.aifactory-cache/

# --- Build / logs -----------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.pid
*.seed
*.tsbuildinfo
coverage/

